rking as intended now.</FONT></td></tr></tbody></table><P><input type=submit value="Vote"><a HREF=http://pub29.ezboard.com/fsilverhawksofdrinalfrm37.showMessage?topicID=6.topic&pollResults=on><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Show results</FONT></A> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub29.ezboard.com/uaguita.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aguita</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 532<br> <font color=#A0B0E0>(4/4/01 12:30:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub29.ezboard.com/fsilverhawksofdrinalfrm37.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Guild Spell/ Gem/ Item Bank</span><hr size=1> Personally, I don't think that spells or quest gems should be sold to guildmates because they're uber rare to rare drops and there are many in the guild who need them.<br>
<br>
To me, it goes along with the looting rules.. I want to give that person that spell because darnit, down the road that spell could save my life or put the extra damage on a big mob to make the raid a success.  <br>
<br>
It's about a family and helping that family out... imho.<br>
<br>
