<br>
If they do NOT have every item they want/need and win a valuable and saleable item via lottery, my guess is that they are going to head to Freeport and attempt to sell or trade out that High Level Drop.<br>
<br>
I'm assuming that Gelmir is referring to a drop occurring during a guild function / hunting party.<br>
<br>
If I acquire an item while hunting with people outside of our guild, I would think that an established guild policy would not apply / compel me to donate said item to S.H. <br>
<br>
I believe the day will come when I have practically all the main items my characters need (I'm not far from it now).<br>
I look forward to becoming more of a philanthropic benefactor.<br>
<br>
My vote, Gelmir, as you might guess, would be in FAVOR of a guild treasury replete with items donated by those who neither need the item nor the plat from sale of said item.  <br>
<br>
My question is, what happens to the 5k pp that Bria paid for the FBSS I donated to the treasury?  If I donate it, I do not want or need the plat.  I would rather see the funds be used to pay for FUN Guild sponsored quests for varying level characters as well as quests that ANY level guild members could participate in. <br>
<br>
Or perhaps I could dictate that the funds be used to buy the Shining Silver and Gold armor that the Order of Champions wear - or perhaps be used to buy low level items that the Order of Champions hand out to lowbies.<br>
<br>
We should be 'thinking outside the box' collectively.<br>
<br>
Shutting up now,<br>
<br>
- Konjur<br>
